---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy" description="DevToolKit Privacy Policy. Your data never leaves your browser.">
  <main class="container static-page-container">
    <div style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: 4rem;">
      <h1>Privacy <span class="gradient-text">Policy</span></h1>
      <p style="font-size: 1.8rem; color: var(--text-secondary); max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto;">
        Last Updated: July 2026
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="glass-panel" style="padding: 4rem; margin-bottom: 4rem;">
      <h2>1. The Short Version</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>We don't collect your data.</strong> Because DevToolKit operates entirely within your web browser using client-side technologies (like WebAssembly and local JavaScript), your code, JSON files, PDFs, and any other inputs never leave your device.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="glass-panel" style="padding: 4rem; margin-bottom: 4rem;">
      <h2>2. What We Do Not Collect</h2>
      <p>We absolutely do <strong>not</strong> collect, process, or store:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Files you upload to our tools (e.g., PDFs, images)</li>
        <li>Text or code you paste into our text areas (e.g., JSON, Base64 strings)</li>
        <li>Personal Identifiable Information (PII)</li>
        <li>Usage analytics or telemetry</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="glass-panel" style="padding: 4rem;">
      <h2>3. Local Storage</h2>
      <p>
        We may use your browser's Local Storage to save user preferences, such as:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Your selected theme (Light/Dark mode)</li>
        <li>Your recently used or favorite tools</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        This information remains on your local device and is never transmitted to us.
      </p>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
